	<objectId>52fd63f9-a7c2-c514-7d41-77880c307287</objectId>
	<internal-name>Sec 1</internal-name>
	<sectionClass_s>no-margin-bottom</sectionClass_s>
	<file-name>52fd63f9-a7c2-c514-7d41-77880c307287.xml</file-name>
	<sectionContent_html>&lt;h2 class="text--md" style="color: var(--color-text-heading); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); line-height: var(--heading-line-height); font-weight: 500; font-size: var(--text-md); font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Does your home office space qualify?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;That depends, and SARS has some specific guidelines for this. Basically, you will need to be able to prove that the space you work from at home, actually qualifies as a &amp;lsquo;home office&amp;rsquo;. The bad news here is that you sitting on your couch with a laptop and Netflix playing in the background, probably doesn&amp;rsquo;t count. These are SARS&amp;rsquo; requirements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style="color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It has to be a dedicated work area that&amp;rsquo;s used exclusively for work purposes on a regular basis. That doesn&amp;rsquo;t mean it has to be an entire room. A part of an existing room is also okay, as long as it meets the rest of the requirements in this list.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You need to have set it up with everything you need, to carry out your specific work and work-related duties. In other words, it must actually look like a serious place that actual work is done in. So, this will mean that it will probably include basics like a desk, an office chair, a computer, an internet connection, etc.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You must have worked from that space for at least six months of the tax year.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;When you need to do your work, you do it primarily (more than 50% of the time) in that space.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 class="text--md" style="color: var(--color-text-heading); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); line-height: var(--heading-line-height); font-weight: 500; font-size: var(--text-md); font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;What can you claim for?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;No, you can&amp;rsquo;t claim for your Youtube premium subscription that you still tell everyone you don&amp;rsquo;t have. SARS is quite strict about what claims it will entertain, and it has published a specific list. Here is the list of home office expenses that are eligible to be claimed against your tax bill:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style="color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rent, or alternatively the interest on your bond.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Stationery, office equipment, and your internet connection&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Wear and tear on office equipment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;The cost of business calls made from your private home telephone&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cleaning&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Cost of repairs to the premises&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Rates and taxes on the premises&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Water and electricity&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Levies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h2 class="text--md" style="color: var(--color-text-heading); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); line-height: var(--heading-line-height); font-weight: 500; font-size: var(--text-md); font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Calculating claimable expenses&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;What&amp;rsquo;s that? You wanted to know how to calculate your claimable expenses relating to your home office? Well, as they say, &amp;lsquo;you got questions, I got answers&amp;rsquo;, and they&amp;rsquo;re right here:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;First, measure up your home office space and note down the total square meterage. Second, measure up your whole house. Or better yet, get your partner to do it while you enjoy some sweet ad-free Youtube premium videos. You know, with that subscription that you still swear to everyone that you never signed up for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Finally, divide your home office space measurement by your whole house measurement. That will give you the percentage size of your home office relative to your house.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;And now, it&amp;rsquo;s time to whip out your calculator.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;List your various expenses, each with its own line total. Then, multiply each of those totals by the percentage number that you just calculated.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;So, for example, if you paid R120 000 in rent for the year, and your home office is 5 square metres, then you&amp;rsquo;ll be eligible to claim R6 000 as a home office expense.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Once you have all of those totals, you can allow for them by filling them in, in the 'Other deductions' section of the 'Home office expenses' block of your tax return. Just bear in mind that the SARS auto assessment won&amp;rsquo;t automatically list these for you. You&amp;rsquo;ll have to add them to your tax return yourself.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Or just use&amp;nbsp;&lt;a style="background-color: transparent;" href="https://www.taxtim.com/za/calculators/home-office-expense-calculator" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;this nifty calculator&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;on the TaxTim website.&lt;/p&gt;</sectionContent_html>
