	</item>	<item datasource="sections" inline="true">	<key>6fbc31bd-14a4-927a-6e24-4338d002ba2a</key>
	<value>Sec 2</value>
<component id="6fbc31bd-14a4-927a-6e24-4338d002ba2a">
	<content-type>/component/component-articlesection</content-type>
	<display-template>/templates/web/components/article-section.ftl</display-template>
	<no-template-required/>
	<merge-strategy>inherit-levels</merge-strategy>
	<objectGroupId>6fbc</objectGroupId>
	<objectId>6fbc31bd-14a4-927a-6e24-4338d002ba2a</objectId>
	<file-name>6fbc31bd-14a4-927a-6e24-4338d002ba2a.xml</file-name>
	<internal-name>Sec 2</internal-name>
	<sectionClass_s>no-margin-bottom</sectionClass_s>
	<sectionContent_html>&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;One then applies this final percentage to the home office expenditure in order to calculate the portion of expenses which is deductible. You allow for this in the &amp;ldquo;Other Deductions&amp;rdquo; section of the ITR12 in the block for Home Office expenses when you complete your tax return.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Remember: these claims will not be listed on your SARS auto assessment and therefore it is important to ensure that you add these to your tax return yourself.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Let&amp;rsquo;s look at an example:&lt;br /&gt;Say your home office is 5 square meters and your total apartment is 100 square meters, then you will be able to claim 5% of household costs as a home office deduction. If you paid R120 000 of rent for the tax year, you will therefore be able to deduct R6 000 as a home office expense. You then use the same approach for the other expenses that you are eligible to claim for.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;You can also use&amp;nbsp;&lt;a style="background-color: transparent;" href="https://www.taxtim.com/za/calculators/home-office-expense-calculator" target="_blank" rel="noopener"&gt;this nifty calculator&lt;/a&gt;&amp;nbsp;that TaxTim developed.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class="text--md" style="color: var(--color-text-heading); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); line-height: var(--heading-line-height); font-weight: 500; font-size: var(--text-md); font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;And what if your employer is reimbursing you for these costs?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;There&amp;rsquo;s a good chance that many of you reading this will be receiving reimbursements from your employer for some of the costs you&amp;rsquo;re incurring in running your home office. The money your employer pays you for these reimbursements is not taxable, provided it meets these requirements:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul style="color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Your employer needs to have given you an instruction to buy those goods or services.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You incurred the costs as a direct result of doing your work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;You are able to prove that the costs you incurred were used only for work purposes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;The types of reimbursed costs that are most often not taxable are data bundles, or internet connection costs, or stationery bought to perform your work tasks.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;We&amp;rsquo;re almost done! So far, we&amp;rsquo;ve looked at what SARS&amp;rsquo; criteria is for a home office space and we&amp;rsquo;ve listed the working from home expenses that may be eligible to be claimed against your tax bill. There&amp;rsquo;s one final bit to talk about and it&amp;rsquo;s something called capital gains tax, or CGT as the nerds call it.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 class="text--md" style="color: var(--color-text-heading); margin-bottom: var(--space-sm); line-height: var(--heading-line-height); font-weight: 500; font-size: var(--text-md); font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;What is capital gains tax &amp;amp; how does it affect my home office?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;It&amp;rsquo;s a tax that is added to your income tax. It's ONLY triggered whenever you sell an asset for a profit and it is calculated based on the profit you made.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;Claiming for a home office tax deduction can decrease your tax liability. In other words, you&amp;rsquo;ll pay less tax. However, there&amp;rsquo;s a big BUT here.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;SARS allows the first R2 million of profit made from selling your home (your &amp;lsquo;primary residence&amp;rsquo;), to be excluded from capital gains tax. However, if you choose to claim for home office expenses, then SARS will exclude your home office space from your primary residence capital gains tax break.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p style="margin-bottom: var(--space-md); line-height: var(--body-line-height); color: #2e2e31; font-family: 'Whitney SSm A', 'Whitney SSm B', system-ui, 'Segoe UI', Roboto, 'Helvetica Neue', Arial, sans-serif, 'Apple Color Emoji', 'Segoe UI Emoji', 'Segoe UI Symbol'; font-size: 14px; background-color: #f9f9f9;"&gt;So in summary, if you choose to go the route of claiming a tax deduction for your home office, then you may lose out when it comes time to sell your house. As with most things tax, it&amp;rsquo;s always best to first consult a tax professional before making any decisions.&lt;/p&gt;</sectionContent_html>
